   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1821-06-07_page02.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1821-06-07">June 7, 1821</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  Dear Sir
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I thank you for writing to me so <choice>
                  <orig>punc-<lb/>
               -tually</orig>
                  <reg>punctually</reg>
               </choice> to inform me of your having<lb/>
               paid my note to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MoilJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi>
                  <unclear>Moilliet</unclear>
               </persName> for<lb/>
               £525: 12: 6. <del>a week before the time</del>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I thank you in the first place you see<lb/>
               for <hi rend="underline">writing punctually</hi> because<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">that</hi> might be some effort to you<lb/>
               - handsome <add>conduct</add> costs you no effort and<lb/>
               perhaps you will not even like to<lb/>
               receive thanks for it - Gratitude <choice>
                  <orig>how<lb/>
               ever</orig>
                  <reg>however</reg>
               </choice> does not simply surprise - I am<lb/>
               delighted that you should have<lb/>
               had - even at the expense of my<lb/>
               mistaking the week in which my <unclear>note</unclear>
               <lb/>
               was payable - This fresh opportunity<lb/>
               of showing me your generous<lb/>
               promptitude.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <del>Though</del> I did forget <unclear>this</unclear>
               <del>day when<lb/>
               my note became due</del>, &amp; <del>
                  <unclear>this</unclear>
               </del> I did<lb/>
               forget whether the money was to<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1821-06-07_page03.jpg"/>

               be paid at <unclear>Hoares</unclear> bank or at your<lb/>
               house &amp; <del>though</del> in fact I was not<lb/>
               aware that my note was ever to be<lb/>
               presented for payment, having<lb/>
               conceived that it was to be in <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MoulJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<lb/>
                  <unclear>Moilliets</unclear>
               </persName> hands till I should write<lb/>
               to let him know that the money<lb/>
               was ready, which I did last week<lb/>
               - But though, I partly from ignora<unclear>nce</unclear>
               <lb/>
               &amp; partly from negligence made<lb/>
               these errors, yet in essential points<lb/>
               my memory for business is good<lb/>
               I remember well that you wrote<lb/>
               when I was abroad last year to say<lb/>
               that you <del>thought</del>
               <add>found</add> the quantity of<lb/>
               the sequel to <title ref="./Workography.xml#Rosam1">Rosamond</title> fell short<lb/>
               of what your printer required and<lb/>
               that you could not afford to give<lb/>
               what had been originally proposed<lb/>
               500<hi rend="superscript">
                  <unclear>£</unclear>
               </hi> for the copy right &amp; in consequence<lb/>
               I promised to deduct if necessary<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1821-06-07_page04.jpg"/>

               a hundred guineas rather than to<lb/>
               extend the work by writing more<lb/>
               in a hurry - I send you a draft<lb/>
               on Hoare for a hundred guineas<lb/>
               &amp; <add>for</add> the odd 12<unclear>
                  <hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
               </unclear>/6 which was tacked<lb/>
               to my note for the price of stamps -<lb/>
            </p>
            <postscript>
               <p>PS If I ought to give you a stamped<lb/>
                  receipt for the copy right of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Rosam1">Rosamond</title>
                  <lb/>
                  let me know or send me a receipt<lb/>
                  on a proper stamp &amp; I will sign it.<lb/>
                  You cannot <del>feel</del>
                  <add>be</add> more delighted<lb/>
                  than I am, I will add than all<lb/>
                  my family feel that my hereditary<lb/>
                  confidence in you ought to continue<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               I am Dear Sir<lb/>
               Your obliged humble <choice>
                  <orig>serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>servant</reg>
               </choice>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1821-06-07_page01.jpg"/>
            <closer>
